def: Pertaining to, or becoming, a feast; festal; joyous; gay;mirthful; sportive.-- Fes"tive*ly, adv.The glad circle round them yield their souls To festive mirth and witthat knows no gall. Thomson.
Having no distinct; without sexual action; as, asexualreproduction. See Fission and Gemmation.
A variety or macaroni made in tubes of small diameter.
A genus of marine bivalve mollusks having thin, delicate, andoften handsomely colored shells.
Water flavored, sweetened, and frozen, to be eaten as aconfection.
Early; soon; in good season.Timely advised, the coming evil shun. Prior.Thanks to you, That called me timelier than my purpose hither, For Ihave gained by it. Shak.
The Australian crested goatsucker (Ægotheles Novæ-Hollandiæ).Also applied to other allied birds, as Podargus Cuveiri.
To cause to pass through a sieve or colander; to strain, asthrough a sieve. [Obs.] Harvey.
